## Research Findings: Tailwind CSS Setup for Astro v6 + Starlight

### 1. **@astrojs/tailwind Integration Status**

**Yes, it exists on npm, but it's DEPRECATED for new projects.**

- Current version: **6.0.2** (last published a year ago)
- Status: Maintained but not recommended for Tailwind CSS v4
- Note: Will continue to work for Tailwind v3/legacy projects, but you should NOT use it for new setups

### 2. **Recommended Setup: Astro v6 + Tailwind CSS v4**

The official recommendation has changed. Use the **@tailwindcss/vite** plugin instead of @astrojs/tailwind.

**Installation (for your Astro Starlight site):**

```bash
pnpm add -D tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite @astrojs/starlight-tailwind
```

**Configuration in `astro.config.mjs`:**

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import starlight from '@astrojs/starlight';
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';

export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [starlight({ /* ... */ })],
  vite: {
    plugins: [tailwindcss()],
  },
});
```

**CSS Setup in `src/styles/global.css`:**

```css
@layer base, starlight, theme, components, utilities;
@import '@astrojs/starlight-tailwind';
@import 'tailwindcss/theme.css' layer(theme);
@import 'tailwindcss/utilities.css' layer(utilities);
```

Then import this CSS file in your layout.

### 3. **@tailwindcss/vite Package**

**Yes, this exists and is fully compatible with Astro v6.**

- It's the **official Tailwind CSS Vite plugin**
- This is now the preferred way to integrate Tailwind v4 with Astro (instead of PostCSS)
- Works seamlessly with Astro's Vite-based build system
- Astro 5.2+ and v6 have native support for this plugin

### Key Advantages of the Vite Approach

- No PostCSS configuration needed
- Better Vite integration (Astro uses Vite)
- Works directly with Tailwind CSS v4
- Simpler setup compared to the deprecated @astrojs/tailwind

### Important Note for Starlight

Since you're using @astrojs/starlight v0.38.2, you'll need the **@astrojs/starlight-tailwind** package to ensure proper CSS layer management and style integration between Starlight and Tailwind.

Sources:

- [Tailwind CSS - Install with Astro](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/installation/framework-guides/astro)
- [Astro - Tailwind Integration Guide](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/integrations-guide/tailwind/)
- [Starlight - CSS and Tailwind Guide](https://starlight.astro.build/guides/css-and-tailwind/)
- [Astro + Tailwind v4 Setup Guide](https://tailkits.com/blog/astro-tailwind-setup/)

